<TEXT>
the armed forces will receive pay 
raises of 20 percent in december with a 100 bonus an official 
report said monday 
soldiers who mounted a fourday uprising this month had demanded 
raises 
the governments news agency telam cited reliable sources 
for its report of the raises it gave no details in its 
twoparagraph story 
the military uprising broke out at a base on the outskirts of the 
capital on dec 1 and moved to another base nearby before the 
mutineers agreed to return to their units the revolt left three 
people dead 
civilian president raul alfonsin denied reports at the time that 
he was forced to make concessions in exchange for the surrender of 
the rebellious troops 
soldiers have complained that they like other public employees 
have lost significant purchasing power as raises failed to keep 
pace with increases in the cost of living 
the military received a 30 percent raise in july and 12 percent 
in october the cost of living rose by 26 percent in july and 9 
percent in october 
the latest raise would be well ahead of inflation which last 
month increased by 6 percent 
the government has tried to control military salaries partly in 
an effort to harness inflation in addition the opposition peronist 
party in congress has blocked the 1988 budget because it wants more 
federal funds for the provinces 
the military share of the total budget has shrunk to about 2 
percent of gross domestic product from about 4 percent during 
military dictatorships of 197683 
</TEXT>
