<TEXT>
a convict dubbed the traveling 
rapist received a stay of execution late monday for the 
rapemurder of a 19yearold woman but a second man was still 
slated to be put to death by injection early tuesday for the killing 
of a restaurateur 
the high court granted an application for a stay of execution for 
samuel hawkins late monday hours after turning down a similar 
request from raymond landry whose execution was still scheduled for 
after midnight 
us supreme court spokeswoman kathy arberg said the application 
was filed at 930 pm est and the order sparing hawkins was entered 
at 1025 pm with chief justice william rehnquist and justice byron 
white dissenting he was sentenced to death for the 1976 
rapeslaying of a 19yearold woman 
earlier monday the nations high court voted 72 to refuse the 
appeal filed by lawyers for landry 39 a native of lafayette 
parish la who was convicted of killing a houston restaurant owner 
during a robbery 
since the supreme court in 1976 allowed capital punishment to 
resume no state has executed two inmates in a single day although 
two inmates and in one case three have been executed on the same 
day in separate states 
before tuesdays scheduled executions 28 inmates including two 
this year had been put to death by texas prison officials since 
1976 the tally is the highest of any state 
before the issuance of a stay the two were to be executed in the 
same death chamber with landry scheduled first 
hawkins 45 faced injection for the rape and stabbing death of 
abbe rogers hamilton of borger who was killed after hawkins entered 
her apparently unlocked home 
hawkins case monday went to the 5th us circuit court of 
appeals in new orleans after a federal district judge in lubbock 
halbert woodward reversed a stay he issued friday state attorneys 
had appealed his action 
hawkins also has a second death sentence for the abduction and 
slaying of a 12yearold amarillo girl he has been dubbed the 
traveling rapist after admitting to some 40 rapes prosecutors 
said 
landrys attorney michael charlton bypassed lower federal 
courts and had appealed directly to the high court 
landry a former electrician was sentenced for the shooting 
death of kosmas prittis prittis 33 a greek immigrant was robbed 
of more than 2300 and fatally shot in the head while he and his 
family were closing their restaurant 
last january landry came within three hours of execution before 
the supreme court issued a stay 
in appeals for each inmate defense attorneys cited a case 
pending before the supreme court involving texas death row inmate 
johnny penry that case challenges the legality of executing 
mentally retarded inmates 
this man isnt retarded assistant attorney general bob walt 
said of landry i dont think thats going to fly with the supreme 
court 
landry an 11thgrade dropout has a lengthy criminal record 
including arrests for sexual assault and abuse of a juvenile 
assault family neglect and petty larceny 
</TEXT>
