<TEXT>
more than 200 cubans came to miami over the weekend 
as part of a program to reunite cubanamericans with relatives who 
left cuba but have been stranded in other countries 
about 190 cubans arrived saturday and an additional 20 arrived 
sunday on flights from spain some 370 more cubans were expected to 
arrive tuesday and thursday on flights sponsored by the cuban 
american national foundation 
the refugees were greeted with cheers as they arrived 
im elated said gilfredo landa 21 as he hugged his 
brothers nelson 19 and yoeidy 14 the two brothers had just 
arrived to join gilfredo who arrived in 1980 during the mariel 
boatlift 
theyre going to learn english he said 
since the foundation program began sept 11 805 former cubans 
have arrived in the united states from panama and costa rica 
under the guidelines of the program relatives or friends of the 
refugees promise to pay travel costs and provide financial support 
for two years 
foundation chairman jorge mas canosa said there will be more 
flights from spain panama costa rica and possibly peru and 
venezuela the foundation can bring up to 1500 refugees into the 
country this year 
</TEXT>
