<TEXT>
more than a dozen flights were delayed at osaka 
international airport when a man broke into a control room and 
disconnected hundreds of fuses from the air traffic control system 
police said today 
the incident cut communications between airport controllers and 
flights using the airport for about 40 minutes on sunday said a 
local police official who spoke on condition of anonymity 
six departures and 11 arrivals were delayed for up to half an 
hour 
police arrested a 26yearold man they described only as a 
professional golfer the official said the man may have entered the 
closely guarded communications control center when employees were at 
lunch 
police using a duplicate key entered and overpowered the man who 
shouted that he was acting at the guidance of jesus christ the 
official said 
his identity was withheld pending investigation of his mental 
health 
</TEXT>
