<TEXT>
more than twice the number of minority high 
school students took advancement placement exams in 1988 than five 
years ago led by a surge among hispanics and asianamericans the 
college board reported 
the boards annual survey of advanced placement tests which high 
school students take to qualify for credit or placement in 
upperlevel college courses also found that california new york 
and florida had by far the most black and hispanic testtakers who 
scored qualifying grades 
in all 288372 students took 419101 advanced placement exams in 
1988 the program sponsored by the college board offers 27 
collegelevel examinations in 16 subjects 
nearly 52000 minority students nationwide took the exams in 
1988 compared with 39517 in 1987 and 142 percent more than the 
21501 who took it five years ago the college board said sunday 
fortynine thousand of those students scored high enough to 
qualify for college credit the tests are scored on a scale of 15 
with colleges usually requiring at least a 3 to qualify for credit 
minority students made up nearly 20 percent of all advanced 
placement testtakers in 1988 compared with 184 percent in 1987 
and 147 percent in 1984 
by using ap to raise the expectations of minority students and 
helping them achieve higher goals schools are bringing more 
minorities into professional and graduate schools said board 
president donald m stewart 
the number of asianamerican students taking the exams was 
27396 up from 21101 in 1987 and 140 percent greater than the 
11413 in 1984 
the number of hispanics taking the test grew 156 percent over 
five years from 5200 to 13322 the number of blacks grew by 135 
percent from 4448 to 10448 
the number of whites taking the tests totaled 210582 up 27 
percent from 165924 in 1987 and 80 percent higher than the 117302 
in 1984 
some 8247 schools offered the exams in 1988 470 more than last 
year 
plano high school near dallas with a student body of 2600 had 
the largest number of advanced placement candidates of any school 
490 and the largest number of tests taken 887 according to the 
report 
california led the nation with 5125 black and hispanic 
testtakers last year new york was second with 2526 followed by 
florida with 2439 
the college board is a nonprofit organization representing 2600 
colleges and other educational groups 
</TEXT>
