to meet the payroll as well as pay for copying research 
telephones rent supplies and the like bush receives a total of 
35 million in public money 
the money is allocated under the presidential transition act of 
1964 the amount was increased this year from the 2 million that 
was allowed when president reagan took office eight years ago 
the bush operation housed in three floors of an office building 
across the street from the hotel where reagan was shot and wounded 
