<TEXT>
illegal fireworks exploded in a crowded street 
market sunday and started a chain reaction and fire that spread to 
five buildings killing at least 61 people and injuring 45 
well be searching all night theyre still finding bodies 
said salvador padillo the red cross commander at the scene 
floodlights lit the narrow street and an alley as rescuers dug 
into the night putting bodies on stretchers tagging them and 
putting them in ambulances a bulldozer began plowing away the 
rubble 
at least 61 people were killed commander enrique mejia 
guadarrama of the red cross said early monday 
they cant get inside the storerooms but they are full of 
bodies said roberto castanon romo city director of medical 
services you can no longer talk of survivors 
at least 11 of the dead were children officials said 
padillo said at least 45 people were injured but an official on 
duty at red cross headquarters put the number at 83 two 
firefighters were among the injured medical workers said 
