ishaq khan swept 78 percent of the presidential vote 
of 446 valid votes ishaq khan polled 348 compared with 91 to his 
nearest rival veteran politican nawabzada nasrullah khan nusrat 
said 
ms bhutto won her first test of strength in the national 
assembly the countrys lower house of parliament 
of 203 members voting on the confidence motion 148 said yes 
and 55 said no 
her pakistan peoples party party emerged as the largest single 
party nov 16 in the countrys first free elections in more than a 
decade but with 105 seats it fell short of an outright majority in 
the 237seat legislature the party since gained support from 
several independents and minor parties 
the constitution dictates that the governing party pass a 
parliamentary test of confidence within 60 days of forming a 
government 
the senate national assembly and four provincial assemblies 
functioned as an electoral college for the president 
provincial assemblies were restricted to 45 votes each to put 
them on equal footing the populous eastern punjab assembly has 260 
members for example compared to western baluchistans 45 
legislators 
