in 1759 100 years after the first jewish families sailed into 
newport the community decided to build a synagogue 
the congregants who by this time numbered 35 families hired 
architect peter harrison 
it is assumed that harrison a quaker who had never seen a 
synagogue based his design on isaac abraham touros description of 
his childhood synagogue in amsterdam touro was the temples cantor 
