individual cells each cell door has a small hole and each inmate 
must put his hands through that hole to be handcuffed before the 
door is opened 
the showers also have bars 
the new oakdale facility will handle prisoners who have been 
sentenced by federal judges to prison terms under construction at 
the site is a 14 million federal deportation center which will 
open in november 1989 to handle detainees 
the rebuilt prison has 265 inmates at this time and can 
accommodate 1300 prison officials said there are 400 guards 
the deportation center will have 1000 beds and perhaps as many 
as another 400 guards said a spokesman for warden oc jenkins 
