<TEXT>
sonja henies icy heart wont be left out in 
the cold when the warehouse where it has been stored for nearly 48 
years is demolished to make room for a frozen foods plant 
the bluegreen ice sculpture was presented to the famous 
norweigian skater and movie star during a valentines day 1941 
performance at the aksarben coliseum the stars one and only 
appearance in omaha 
miss henie said she would return for it some day but she died in 
1969 without ever claiming what cbs newsman charles kuralt once 
called the longestrunning openended most enduring publicity 
stunt of all time 
barney oldfield who was an army publicist when he carved the 
heart said miss henie found her appearance in omaha less than 
heartwarming among other things he said she was upset that high 
costs cut into her profits 
all she was really interested in that night was to get it 
out of the dressing room because it had greenblue dye and it was 
dripping on her dressing room floor oldfield now an executive 
for litton industries said in a telephone interview from his 
beverly hills calif office 
so the heart was taken to the omaha cold storage co warehouse 
near the mississippi river and there it has remained over the 
years gaining in notoriety as it shrunk from its original 100 
pounds to about 60 pounds 
it is highly flattering that something made 45 years ago out of 
the most perishable substance on earth frozen water would still 
be in existence in a cold storage warehouse in omaha oldfield 
said 
when plans were announced to tear down the warehouse to make way 
for a new conagra frozen foods complex there was some concern about 
the fate of the heart but roy mattson owner of omaha cold storage 
said he has moved the sculpture to his companys new warehouse in a 
converted meatpacking plant 
its in a box in a room with a lot of raw materials for making 
pet food liver salisbury glands items like that mattson said 
id hate to throw it away id probably get in trouble 
i suppose some goodhearted guy will continue to take care of 
it oldfield said it has been kind of like a relay race there 
have been 10 or 12 people who had custody of it from one time to 
another 
oldfield born in elk creek neb said he hoped to visit the 
heart during a trip to omaha later this month he recalled how the 
ice shows promoter approached him in 1941 about a publicity stunt 
but warned oldfield that miss henie wasnt always friendly 
oldfield carved the heart out of a keg of ice and presented it to 
miss henie at the valentine show as the promoter had warned 
however she gave oldfield the cold shoulder 
as kind of an exit line i said we would keep it until she came 
back to omaha again oldfield said 
we put it in the back of a pickup it was 10 degrees below 
