a moderate earthquake rocked portions of 
southeast alaska early monday rattling windows but causing no 
reported damage or injuries the alaska tsunami warning center 
reported 
geophysicist paul whitmore said the 957 am ast temblor 
measured 47 on the richter scale it was centered about 90 miles 
northwest of juneau or 40 miles west of haines he said 
the quake rattled windows in juneau and haines he said 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 time 
stronger than one of 65 
the 1964 good friday earthquake in alaska measured 85 on the 
richter scale and was centered in prince william sound it generated 
large waves that devastated several coastal communities and killed 
114 people as far south as oregon and hawaii 
