that rejects many of the modernizing reforms of the second vatican 
council 196265 
he was excommunicated after he consecrated four bishops without 
papal approval in switzerland in june causing the first schism in 
the church in more than a century the vatican has warned lefebvres 
followers that they also face excommunication if they adhere to the 
schism 
but the pope has promised to meet their traditionalist needs 
including wider use of the 16th century latin mass if they remain 
loyal to rome 
