<TEXT>
three trains crashed into each other near a busy 
south london junction during rush hour monday morning hurling 
bodies onto the tracks as the cars split open like a ripe 
tomato officials said they counted 36 dead 
more than 110 of the estimated 1500 passengers on the trains 
were hospitalized 32 with serious injuries such as multiple 
fractures crushed abdomens and amputations hospital and ambulance 
officials said 
the british railways board said a preliminary investigation cast 
blame on a technical fault that arose after work on signaling 
equipment 
it is sheer bloody hell thats what it is said jim 
mcmillan london fire brigades assistant chief officer surveying 
the scene at the clapham junction one of europes busiest train 
crossways 
police and fire brigade officials said 34 people died in the 
crash and two died later at a hospital bringing the death toll to 
36 
some bodies were so badly dismembered that limbs were placed in 
separate body bags adding to confusion about the toll said john 
norris a fire brigade divisional officer police inspector barry 
webb said some limbs were unaccounted for and therefore the toll 
could rise 
the accident occurred just before 8 am when a londonbound 
commuter train slammed into the rear of another passenger train that 
was stopped about 400 yards south of clapham junction the two 
trains were packed with 1500 people many of whom were standing 
rescue efforts began but an empty freight train on an adjacent 
line then plowed into spillover wreckage and apparently hit some 
passengers who had scrambled onto the tracks bodies were cut in 
half limbs were thrown around by the impact said robin winch a 
doctor 
three cars hurtled into the air and onto an embankment and eight 
overturned 
a fourth train crowded with commuters stopped a few feet short 
of the wreck british rail said 
rescue teams working under arc lights used heavy lifting 
equipment and hydraulic jacks through the early morning hours 
tuesday searching the mangled debris for more trapped victims 
many passengers dazed or slightly injured were able to walk 
away but london ambulance service spokesman chris webb said 114 
passengers were taken to five local hospitals 30 with serious 
injuries and others were treated on the scene 
dozens of passengers were trapped some for up to five hours 
waiting for rescue workers to hack through dense underbrush 
alongside the tracks and to pry open roofs of overturned carriages 
others walked away in search of other transport to their jobs in 
london a man clutched a crushed briefcase to his chest another in 
a smart business suit carried a bloodspattered raincoat 
seats were snapped from their mountings and strewn alongside the 
wreckage briefcases newspapers and business documents littered the 
track and the embankment a childs stroller lay atop one carriage 
lou gill the fire brigades chief divisional officer said all 
survivors were rescued by 1 pm but he feared there may be 
further bodies underneath the wreckage 
it was the worst train wreck in britain since 1975 when 43 died 
in a subway that crashed in a london tunnel fortynine people were 
killed in a 1967 when a train derailed in south london 
transport minister paul channon promised a full inquiry 
opposition labor party lawmakers and railroad union leaders demanded 
that the inquiry examine allegations of overcrowding and cuts in 
safety spending on stateowned british rail the trains are not part 
of londons subway system 
rescue workers many visibly distraught used infrared cameras 
metal cutters and cranes to free passengers emergency surgery 
including amputations were performed on the scene operations 
continued after nightfall bathed in floodlights 
bodies were ripped apart and the trains were tangled 
together said firefighter chris fitzgerald we had to use our 
heaviest cutting gear and it was like nibbling away at the wreckage 
just a little at a time 
there were pieces of bodies lying all over the place you could 
hear people moaning said webb of the ambulance service 
passenger chris reeves was in the buffet car of the moving train 
when the crash occurred and the roof split open like a ripe 
tomato 
there was furniture and enormous lumps of metal flying 
everywhere he said we tried to find people underneath the 
rubble but there was so much debris there was nothing we could do 
the emmanuel high school near the scene of the crash was 
transformed into a makeshift clinic for scores of walking injured 
schoolboys scrambled down the banks to help rescue survivors 
queen elizabeth ii and archbishop of canterbury robert runcie 
expressed grief and condolences prime minister margaret thatcher 
said she was griefstricken 
british rail and the national union of railwaymen said they would 
hold their own inquiries 
mondays accident is the third serious train crash in britain in 
the last month on nov 30 15 passengers were injured in a crash 
outside newcastleupontyne and on nov 12 a driver was killed and 
18 passengers hurt in a derailment near st helens in northwest 
england 
britains worst crash occurred in may 1915 when 227 people were 
killed and 246 injured in a collision between a troop train and 
passenger train at gretna green southwest scotland 
