the naked gun 
 
when was the last time you had some real fun at a movie if you 
have to stop and think then run dont walk to the nearest theater 
showing the naked gun from the files of police squad 
be prepared for a zany sidesplitting collection of gags some 
of them off color and most of them outrageous and get ready to give 
your laugh muscles a workout 
naked gun is the latest product of those masters of hilarity 
david zucker jim abrahams and jerry zucker who gave us the 
memorable airplane and the notsomemorable top secret 
this time theyre parodying one of their own failures the short 
lived tv series police squad 
tried and true leslie nielsen is back as the unsmiling klutz of 
the police world lt frank drebin who smashes police cars into 
trash cans gets his hand stuck in a fish tank and falls over his 
own feet in the pursuit of justice hes wonderful 
drebin trying to foil a plot on the life of queen elizabeth ii 
sets off a series of hilarious nonstop gags for instance he winds 
up as the singer of the national anthem and the umpire at a major 
league baseball game where reggie jackson plays an unexpected role 
as assassininwaiting 
david zuckers direction of these complex sight gags is flawless 
priscilla presley is drebins romantic interest jane spencer 
whose deadpan delivery is a match for nielsens a scene in which 
the two practice safe sex in body size condoms is typical of the 
giggle power of this film 
there is a villain played by a silky ricardo montalban a 
bemused sidekick played by george kennedy and lots of celebrity 
cameos as well as a dumpy queen elizabeth lookalike 
there are no messages here and the story is just an excuse for 
some terrific jokes call it slapstick call it crazy call it a hit 
naked gun is rated pg13 for language double entendres and 
implied nudity the very young might wonder why the adults are 
falling on the floor laughing 
by linda deutsch associated press writer 
