<TEXT>
the dollar strengthened marginally against major 
foreign currencies monday but exchange dealers said trading was 
extremely slow reflecting a reluctance to do business in advance of 
the governments marketmoving monthly trade report 
gold prices eased republic national bank quoted bullion at 
42025 a troy ounce as of 4 pm est down from 42250 late friday 
currency strategists read little significance into the dollars 
small gain saying it largely was due to internal market influences 
of supply and demand not any outside news 
but some said speculation that the federal reserve would move to 
tighten interest rates may have strengthened the dollar a bit 
higher interest rates make dollardenominated investments more 
attractive 
many dealers said the overwhelming force shaping the markets 
behavior was reticence to take any risky positions before the 
commerce departments report on the october trade deficit due 
wednesday 
the highly unpredictable monthly trade numbers are seen as one of 
the most visible symbols of us economic strength and 
competitiveness abroad with an enormous potential to influence 
financial markets 
a large trade deficit would likely depress the dollars value 
while a small deficit would help stabilize or boost the currency 
in tokyo the dollar rose 049 yen to close at 12292 yen later 
in london the dollar was quoted at 12283 yen by the time trading 
